<TEXT>
here is a brief summary of events in romania 
the 24year reign of president nicolae ceausescu collapsed as a 
citizen uprising was joined by rebellious troops a top defense 
official who joined the rebels said they controlled most of the 
country with only scattered resistance 
ceausescu and his wife elena fled the presidential palace by 
helicopter some reports said they had been arrested others 
indicated their whereabouts were unknown 
ceausescus son the interior minister the chief of the secret 
police and other key figures of the regime were arrested 
fighting continued into saturday between rebel troops and 
security forces loyal to ceausescu in bucharest and elsewhere in 
the country 
hundreds were reported killed in the fighting in addition to 
the thousands believed killed earlier in the week of unrest 
a national salvation committee was formed to run the country 
temporarily 
jubilant romanians rallied in bucharest and throughout the 
country 
hundreds of people dug up mass graves near timisoara in 
western romania in search of as many as 4500 people killed last 
weekend when protesters were massacred by security forces 
the bush administration said a terrible burden had been 
lifted from the romanian people and expressed hope for a peaceful 
transition to democracy 
the european community foreign ministers pledged immediate aid 
to romania and the red cross in geneva flew four tons of medical 
supplies to bucharest 
</TEXT>
