ernest sisto an awardwinning photographer who 
spent 49 years with the new york times died at his home friday at 
age 85 
sisto was known for his baseball photos and he was friendly 
with new york yankees stars joe dimaggio and phil rizzuto he 
covered many major sporting events including the world series and 
the kentucky derby 
sisto was honored for his work by everybody from the press 
photographers association to a cigar manufacturer 
he is survived by his wife amelia and two sons daniel and 
ernest jr 
