<TEXT>
christmas and new years weekend traffic 
accidents may claim as many as 770 lives this holiday season 
according to statisticians at the national safety council 
the chicagobased council issued its annual estimate thursday 
basing it on data from previous years seasonal weather factors and 
national driving safety trends 
the council said alcohol a factor in more than half of all 
fatal crashes is a particular threat over the holidays when 
parties can lead to overindulgence 
the council estimated between 320 and 420 people would die in 
vehicular crashes during the official christmas period which 
begins at 6 pm est on friday and ends at 1159 pm local time 
monday 
an additional 15000 to 19000 people may suffer disabling 
injuries during the period the council said 
during last years christmas holiday 386 people died and some 
17900 were injured 
for the new years holiday period which begins at 6 pm est 
friday dec 29 and runs through 1159 pm local time monday 
jan 1 the council predicted between 250 and 350 fatalities plus 
from 12000 to 16000 disabling injuries 
last year 317 people died and about 14700 suffered disabling 
injuries over the new years period 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

