<DOCNO> AP891222-0082 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
here are some key dates for change in eastern europe this year 
aug 1819 polands leader gen wojciech jaruzelski 
announces the first noncommunist government in poland since world 
war ii nominating solidarity activist tadeusz mazowiecki as prime 
minister after solidarity swept june elections 
oct 7 the communist party in hungary formally disbands 
reconstituting itself as hungarian socialist party parliament 
rewrites the constitution and adopts laws allowing several parties 
to contest free elections next year 
nov 9 east germany lifts travel restrictions and opens 
gateways through berlin wall three weeks after resignation of 
communist party chief erich honecker who supervised the building 
of the wall in 1961 honeckers handpicked replacement egon krenz 
and the ruling party politburo resigns a month later after 
parliament voted to eliminate the partys constitutionally 
guaranteed hold on power 
nov 10 communist party chief todor zhivkov of bulgaria is 
ousted and replaced by a moderate 
nov 29 in czechoslovakia parliament deletes the leading role 
of the communist party from the constitution after massive protests 
force the resignations of hardline party chief milos jakes and the 
politburo 
dec 22 president nicolae ceausescu of romania the last 
hardline ruler in the soviet bloc is overthrown by a weeklong 
popular revolt during which hundreds of demonstrators were killed 
by security forces 
</TEXT>
