<TEXT>
thousands of jubilant berliners surged 
through new openings in the berlin wall at the brandenburg gate 
today for the first time in 28 years 
the celebrants braved an intermittent rain as they filled the 
square in front of the towering symbol of the postwar division of 
germany that is becoming a monument to the rapprochement of east 
germany and west germany 
east german premier hans modrow met west germany chancellor 
helmut kohl at the border for the 3 pm 9 am est ceremony 
then they walked together into east germany they were nearly 
mobbed by the crowd as they walked to a platform in front of the 
