hanukkah marks the victory of the jews over the grecosyrian 
kingdom in 165 bc the kingdom had tried to impose its culture on 
the jews and desecrated the holy temple in jerusalem with statues 
of greek gods jews rose in revolt and drove out the syrians 
according to legend when the jews entered jerusalem and tried 
to rekindle the temples eternal flame they found enough oil for 
only one day but the oil miraculously lasted eight days 
to commemorate the miracle jews light candles at sunset for 
eight consecutive days the candles are placed in an eightbranch 
candelabra called a menorah 
one candle is lighted the first day and a new candle is used 
each day until eight burn in the menorah 
