a meeting of all political parties 
friday nominated opposition leader vaclav havel for president and 
alexander dubcek as parliament chairman the official news agency 
ctk reported 
havel a dissident playwright whose works were banned emerged 
as the opposition leader during a peaceful revolution that began in 
midnovember and ended four decades of communist rule 
dubcek was communist party chief in 1968 and led the prague 
spring of reform that was crushed by a sovietled invasion 
