inviting panama to speak on the invasion but disagreeing over which 
of the rival ambassadors should be given the floor 
on thursday night the council voted 140 with the united 
states abstaining to hear panamas views but did not decide who 
was the legitimate ambassador the council then met in private 
friday to continue arguing the issue 
