<TEXT>
bond prices fell friday in abbreviated 
preholiday trading on a lower dollar overseas concerns over 
japanese interest rates and a buoyant report on us durable goods 
orders 
the treasurys benchmark 30year bond declined 516 point or 
313 per 1000 in face amount its yield which rises when prices 
fall jumped to 788 percent from 785 percent late thursday 
the credit markets shut down at 1 pm est in advance of the 
christmas and hanukkah holidays 
william v sullivan director of moneymarket research for dean 
witter reynolds inc said dealers sold bonds in an effort to 
reduce their portfolios before the end of the year 
he said a drop in the dollar in overseas trading also spurred 
some selling as did concern that japan may raise its key lending 
rate by half a percentage point over the long holiday weekend 
the us financial markets are closed monday for christmas 
economists said fridays report showing orders for durable goods 
costly items expected to last more than three years up 51 
percent in november caused an immediate selloff the increase was 
the biggest in a year and averted the first threemonth drop since 
mid1986 
the november durable goods gain was an exception to recent 
evidence that the us manufacturing sector is in a severe slowdown 
it seemed to suggest that although there are pockets of 
weakness in the economy were not in a position that would 
indicate that a recession is at hand sullivan said 
an economic slowdown generally boosts demand for longterm 
fixedincome investments such as bonds which are seen as a hedge 
against hard times 
kathleen camilli a moneymarket economist with drexel burnham 
lambert inc said the increase in durable goods orders was sharply 
higher than economists projections ranging from no increase to up 
05 percent 
in the secondary market for treasury securities prices of 
shortterm government issues fell 732 point to point 
intermediate maturities were down 516 point to 1332 point and 
longterm issues were 932 point lower according to telerate inc 
a financial information service 
the movement of a point is equivalent to a change of 10 in the 
price of a bond with a 1000 face value 
the shearson lehman hutton daily treasury bond index which 
measures price movements on all outstanding treasury issues with 
maturities of a year or longer fell 336 to 119416 
yields on threemonth treasury bills rose to 782 percent as the 
discount gained 3 basis points to 758 percent yields on sixmonth 
bills rose to 783 percent as the discount increased 7 basis points 
to 744 percent yields on oneyear bills jumped to 769 percent as 
the discount rose 5 basis points to 716 percent 
a basis point is onehundredth of a percentage point the yield 
is the annualized return on an investment in a treasury bill the 
discount is the percentage that bills are selling below the face 
value which is paid at maturity 
the federal funds rate the interest on overnight loans between 
banks was quoted at 8 316 percent down from 8 percent late 
thursday 
in the taxexempt market the bond buyer index of 40 actively 
traded municipal bonds closed at 93 down 132 point the average 
yield to maturity held at 722 percent late thursday 
